00:10:46,91 --> 00:10:49,14
Two babies?
两个宝宝？

166
00:10:49,38 --> 00:10:51,44
You know,a boy and a girl.
对，一男一女

167
00:10:51,71 --> 00:10:55,05
Hopefully,the girl will come first, so Ben won't feel competitive.
我希望先生女的，所以小班 不会觉得有太大的竞争

168
00:10:57,82 --> 00:10:59,58
Then what's gonna happen?
那接下来呢？

169
00:10:59,79 --> 00:11:03,81
We won't wanna raise kids in the city, so we'll move to Scarsdale.
我们不希望孩子在城市里长大 所以我们或许会搬到史卡戴

170
00:11:05,83 --> 00:11:09,23
We'll be far enough from our parents so we don't have to see them...
我们会住得离我们的父母够远 所以不用常常看到他们…

171
00:11:09,50 --> 00:11:11,83
... but close enough that they can baby-sit.
…但又不会太远 所以随时可以请他们来带小孩

172
00:11:12,07 --> 00:11:16,26
And yes,I know the taxes are a little higher than Nassau County...
没错，我知道那里的税 是比那梭郡要高一点…

173
00:11:16,50 --> 00:11:18,50
... but the school system's great.
…但学校制度据说非常非常棒

174
00:11:21,81 --> 00:11:24,07
Wow,that's great! Great!
太棒了…

175
00:11:24,91 --> 00:11:26,90
Okay,wow! You know what?
你知道吗？

176
00:11:27,11 --> 00:11:29,01
I'm off my break now.
我休息完了

177
00:11:30,35 --> 00:11:31,91
Here. You take this.
所以你拿着

178
00:11:34,42 --> 00:11:37,82
I'm gonna go pour these very nice people some coffee.
我要去帮这些好人倒咖啡了

179
00:11:38,86 --> 00:11:40,83
Look at that. I don't have a pot.
你瞧瞧，我没有咖啡壶

180
00:11:41,03 --> 00:11:43,46
I don't have a pot. Maybe I've got one at home.
或许我家里有一个

181
00:11:43,70 --> 00:11:46,00
Or in Scarsdale. Hey,is that a door?
或是史卡戴，那是门吗？

182
00:11:52,81 --> 00:11:54,57
Hey,Pheebs. What's happening?
菲菲，怎么了？

183
00:11:54,81 --> 00:11:58,40
Murder,cancer,soccer teams eating each other in the Andes.
谋杀，癌症 足球队在安地斯山脉吃来吃去

184
00:12:00,35 --> 00:12:02,08
So you watched the movies?
你看了电影了？

185
00:12:02,35 --> 00:12:04,84
What is happening to the world?
这个世界到底怎么了？

186
00:12:05,32 --> 00:12:08,25
I mean.... No,no,because E.T. Ieaves...
我是说，因为ET走了…

187
00:12:08,46 --> 00:12:11,15
...and Rocky loses. Charlotte dies.
…洛基输了，夏绿蒂死了

188
00:12:11,49 --> 00:12:12,79
Charlotte who?
哪个夏绿蒂？

189
00:12:13,03 --> 00:12:14,46
With the web. The spider.
跟蛛网，那只蜘蛛

190
00:12:14,66 --> 00:12:16,69
She dies. She has babies and dies.
它死了，它生了宝宝后就死了

191
00:12:16,93 --> 00:12:19,99
It's like,"Welcome home from the hospital." Thud!
那就像…“欢迎从医院回来”

192
00:12:21,77 --> 00:12:23,43
You wanna feel better?
想不想舒服一点？

193
00:12:26,11 --> 00:12:28,63
Here. Watch this.
来，看这个

194
00:12:28,88 --> 00:12:31,44
It's a Wonderful Life. I've heard of this.
“人生真美妙”这个我听说过

195
00:12:31,68 --> 00:12:34,27
So you can't lose. It's there in the title.
所以没问题，片名说明了一切

196
00:12:34,48 --> 00:12:36,21
Wonderfulness is baked right in.
包你美妙得不得了

197
00:12:36,45 --> 00:12:38,85
I fell for that with Pride of the Yankees.
拜托，我差点就被 “北方佬的骄傲”给骗了

198
00:12:39,12 --> 00:12:41,11
I thought I'd see a film about Yankee pride.
我以为我要看的是 关于“北方佬的骄傲”

199
00:12:41,32 --> 00:12:44,22
And boom! The guy gets Lou Gehrig's disease.
然后… 那个砘锏昧寺犯鹑鹬

200
00:12:46,19 --> 00:12:50,46
The guy was Lou Gehrig. Didn't you kind of see it coming?
那个砘锝新犯鹑 你没预感吗？

201
00:12:52,47 --> 00:12:55,23
Watch that. It'll restore all your faith in humanity.
你看就是了，我保证能 让你恢复对人类的信心

202
00:12:56,40 --> 00:12:58,00
Hey,big guy. Game time.
大个儿，球赛时间到了

203
00:12:58,31 --> 00:13:01,04
-Hey! Be right there! -There's a game?
好，马上来 有球赛

204
00:13:01,24 --> 00:13:04,51
I just got my Pik-Up Stiks back from the shop.
对，我刚从店里 拿了棍子玩具回来

205
00:13:05,65 --> 00:13:07,64
Bring your nerves of steel.
带着你的铁胆来

206
00:13:09,98 --> 00:13:11,92
It's the basketball playoffs.
是篮球决赛

207
00:13:12,15 --> 00:13:16,59
I appreciate this,but you don't have to hang out with them for me.
亲爱的，我不喜欢你这样 但是你不用为了我跟他们混

208
00:13:16,82 --> 00:13:18,26
They have each other.
反正他们两个可以做伴

209
00:13:18,49 --> 00:13:20,69
Oh,no,honey. I mean,don't worry.
不，亲爱的，别担心

210
00:13:20,93 --> 00:13:24,83
I like hanging out with them. They're different than my other friends.
我很喜欢跟他们混，很好玩 他们跟我别的朋友不同

211
00:13:25,03 --> 00:13:29,06
They don't start sentences with "You know who just died shoveling snow?"
他们不会一见面就说 “你知道谁铲雪时死了吗？”

212
00:13:30,37 --> 00:13:32,57
All right,that's great. Then just go.
好吧，那就去吧

213
00:13:33,34 --> 00:13:34,77
Go Nicks!
加油，尼克队

214
00:13:35,01 --> 00:13:36,70
It's the college playoffs.
是大学篮球决赛

215
00:13:36,94 --> 00:13:39,34
-Then,go Vassar! -They're not in it.
加油，瓦萨 他们没比

216
00:13:39,55 --> 00:13:41,38
Okay,then just go.
那加油吧

217
00:13:43,75 --> 00:13:45,58
Why does this bother me so much?
我为什么要那么在意呢？

218
00:13:45,85 --> 00:13:50,52
I'm not one of those people who wants to spend 24 hours a day together.
我并不想当那种要男友 24小时都跟她们在一起的人

219
00:13:50,72 --> 00:13:51,92
Sure.
对呀

220
00:13:52,13 --> 00:13:55,25
He just doesn't have much free time. What do I do?
只是他空闲的时间不多 我不知道，我到底该怎么办？

221
00:13:55,46 --> 00:13:59,42
Does it matter? You'll just die or divorce or blow your pet's head off.
有关系吗？你始终都会死 或离婚，或枪杀你的宠物

222
00:14:03,57 --> 00:14:04,47
Me too!
我也是

223
00:14:04,71 --> 00:14:08,11
Rachel,I got a question. Richard made plans again with the guys
瑞秋，我有个问题 理查又跟他们做计划了…

224
00:14:08,31 --> 00:14:10,28
Ross made plans for the century.
对，罗斯刚计划了整个世纪

225
00:14:10,61 --> 00:14:14,57
I'm gonna go read Cosmo. Maybe there's something helpful in it.
我想我要回房去看杂志了 或许会读到什么有用的

226
00:14:14,78 --> 00:14:19,55
If not,I can learn how to do a bikini wax with leftover Christmas candles.
不然至少可以学会 怎样用圣诞树剩下的蜡烛除毛

227
00:14:22,59 --> 00:14:24,46
What happened back there?
你刚刚是怎么回事？

228
00:14:24,73 --> 00:14:26,45
I don't know. You tell me.
不知道，你告诉我吧

229
00:14:26,66 --> 00:14:29,42
One minute I'm holding Ben, then I've got two kids...
我刚刚还像抱足球一样抱着班 接下来我就有两个孩子…

230
00:14:29,63 --> 00:14:32,60
... I'm living in Scarsdale complaining about taxes!
…住在史卡戴，抱怨着税太高

231
00:14:32,83 --> 00:14:35,43
Well,I'm sorry. I think about stuff.
那抱歉，我就是爱东想西想

232
00:14:35,67 --> 00:14:39,30
You're at work,you're assembling bones, your mind wanders.
我是说，工作的时候 一边弄骨头就会一边乱想嘛

233
00:14:39,51 --> 00:14:43,17
You've planned out the next 20 years. We've dated for six weeks!
你计划了我们往后二十年生活 我们才在一起六周

234
00:14:43,41 --> 00:14:45,40
You never think about our future?
你从不想未来的事吗？

235
00:14:45,65 --> 00:14:48,67
I think about whose apartment we'll sleep at tomorrow...
想，但我想的是 我们明晚住谁那边好…

236
00:14:48,92 --> 00:14:50,91
...and where we'll have dinner next Saturday!
…下个礼拜六晚上 我们去哪里吃晚饭

237
00:14:51,12 --> 00:14:53,64
I do not think about our children's names!
我不会去想 我们的孩子会叫什么名字

238
00:14:55,02 --> 00:14:57,65
You know what our children's names will be?
你知道我们的孩子 会叫什么名字？

239
00:14:58,69 --> 00:15:03,13
No,I mean,you know. I read a book, and there was a girl named Emily.
不…我…我是说我看到一本书 里头有个女孩叫蜜莉

240
00:15:03,33 --> 00:15:05,53
And I thought that might be good.
我觉得…我觉得还不错

241
00:15:07,50 --> 00:15:08,37
What book?
哪一本书？

242
00:15:09,70 --> 00:15:11,53
The Big Book of Children's Names.
“儿童命名大观”

243
00:15:14,21 --> 00:15:15,33
Okay,listen.
你听着

244
00:15:15,61 --> 00:15:17,04
What we have is amazing.
我们在一起很棒

245
00:15:17,28 --> 00:15:20,01
But I do not want everything decided for me!
但我不要别人为我决定好一切

246
00:15:20,21 --> 00:15:21,88
I spent my whole life like that.
我那样过一辈子了

247
00:15:22,15 --> 00:15:24,67
It's what I had with Barry. That's a reason I left.
我跟贝利就是那样 那是我离开的原因之一

248
00:15:24,89 --> 00:15:26,85
I like not knowing right now.
我喜欢有未知

249
00:15:27,19 --> 00:15:31,12
Sorry if that scares you,but if you wanna be with me,deal with that!
如果那样吓着了你，那很抱歉 但若你要跟我在一起就接受吧

250
00:15:31,33 --> 00:15:33,02
-Okay,fine! -Thank you!
好，很好 谢谢

251
00:15:33,23 --> 00:15:35,70
-We're not done! -I didn't know that.
还没完呢 那我不知道

252
00:15:36,16 --> 00:15:40,19
You're with a guy who won't stop planning his future with you.
跟你在一起的人 不会停止去计划他跟你的未来

253
00:15:40,40 --> 00:15:42,23
He knows we'll end up together.
因为他知道我们最后会在一起

254
00:15:42,50 --> 00:15:45,56
If that scares you,tough! You'll have to deal with that.
如果你害怕了，很不幸 因为你必须学会接受

255
00:15:45,81 --> 00:15:47,74
-I will! -Good,because I love you!
很好，我会的 好，因为我爱你

256
00:15:48,01 --> 00:15:49,53
Oh,yeah? I love you too!
是吗？我也爱你

257
00:15:49,74 --> 00:15:51,97
-That's the first time we've said that! -Yes,it is!
我们第一次互相说我爱你 没错

258
00:15:52,18 --> 00:15:54,67
-I'm gonna kiss you! -You better!
那我就要亲你了 最好是这样

259
00:16:02,59 --> 00:16:04,15
Thanks for the great movie tip.
谢谢你给我的建议

260
00:16:04,36 --> 00:16:06,22
-Did you like it? -Oh,yeah.
你喜欢吗？ 喜欢

261
00:16:06,43 --> 00:16:09,92
I don't know if I was happier when George Bailey destroyed the business...
我不知道我是该在 贝乔治毁了家庭事业之后…

262
00:16:10,20 --> 00:16:14,10
...or Donna Reed cried or when the pharmacist made his ear bleed.
…还是在李唐娜哭是在药剂师 害他耳朵流血时会比较快乐

263
00:16:16,00 --> 00:16:18,77
I'll give you the ear thing, but wasn't the ending wonderful?
好吧，我选耳朵流血 你不觉得结局满好的吗？

264
00:16:19,21 --> 00:16:21,17
I didn't watch it. I was too depressed.
结局我根本就没看 我太沮丧了

265
00:16:21,41 --> 00:16:23,67
It kept getting worse! It should've been called:
剧情越来越叫人家失望 这片子应该叫：

266
00:16:23,91 --> 00:16:28,21
"It's a Sucky Life,And Just When You Think It Can't Suck Anymore,It Does!"
“人生真衰就在你觉得 无法更衰时，它更衰”

267
00:16:30,95 --> 00:16:32,38
IKick,save! And...
我踢球…

268
00:16:32,62 --> 00:16:33,88
...denied!
…接住

269
00:16:34,62 --> 00:16:37,95
He gets it back. Pass to the middle,lines it up....
但他抢回来，传到中间 然后准备踢，碰…

270
00:16:38,86 --> 00:16:39,72
Yes!
太棒了！

271
00:16:39,93 --> 00:16:43,02
Could that shot be any prettier?
那球还可以踢得更漂亮吗？

272
00:16:43,70 --> 00:16:45,26
Man,you are incredible.
老兄，你真厉害

273
00:16:45,47 --> 00:16:47,23
We had a table in college.
我们大学时也有这玩意儿

274
00:16:47,43 --> 00:16:50,70
Really? I didn't know they had foosball in the 1800s.
我不晓得 1800年也有桌上足球

275
00:16:51,44 --> 00:16:55,53
Nice mustache. At puberty, that thing will really kick in.
对了，你的胡子不错 青春期一到就会茂盛起来

276
00:16:59,65 --> 00:17:03,31
Not to sound too Florence Henderson, but dinner's on the table.
我也不想太像个好太太 但晚餐做好了

277
00:17:03,55 --> 00:17:04,57
One more point.
再玩一下

278
00:17:07,65 --> 00:17:08,88
Score!
得分

279
00:17:10,46 --> 00:17:11,98
Now can we go?
可以走了吗？

280
00:17:12,63 --> 00:17:14,75
That's why we don't let her play.
看吧，所以我们才不让她玩

281
00:17:17,06 --> 00:17:18,66
Is everything all right?
一切都还好吧？

282
00:17:21,40 --> 00:17:23,50
Don't be mad at him. It's our fault.
听我说，别跟他生气 是我们的错

283
00:17:23,74 --> 00:17:25,67
I'm sorry we've been hogging his time.
我们占了他太多时间了

284
00:17:25,94 --> 00:17:28,00
He's just really great to hang out with.
是呀，跟他真的是很棒

285
00:17:28,24 --> 00:17:29,40
-Well.... -No,seriously.
这个嘛… 不…说真的

286
00:17:29,61 --> 00:17:33,17
We just talked about this. He is so much cooler than our dads.
我跟钱德刚才还在说 他比我们的爸爸酷多了

287
00:17:36,15 --> 00:17:38,95
Our dads are okay and all, but Richard is just
我是说我们爸爸是还好啦 可是理查好…

288
00:17:39,15 --> 00:17:40,81
What are you kicking me for?
你踢我干什么？

289
00:17:42,52 --> 00:17:44,82
I'm trying to talk here.
我正在讲话，你…

290
00:17:47,26 --> 00:17:49,16
You guys see me as a dad?
你们觉得我是父字辈的？

291
00:17:49,36 --> 00:17:51,30
-Oh,yeah! -No!
对呀 不

292
00:17:55,04 --> 00:17:59,17
You're just clearly not familiar with our young persons' vernacular.
你很显然不了解 我们年轻人的用语

293
00:17:59,44 --> 00:18:02,53
When we say "dad," we mean "buddy."
我们“爸爸”的意思是指兄弟

294
00:18:03,61 --> 00:18:05,31
We mean "pal."
是“伙伴”的意思

295
00:18:05,51 --> 00:18:08,31
No,seriously. Joey's my dad.
我说真的，乔伊他是我爸

296
00:18:11,05 --> 00:18:12,88
Monica's my dad.
摩妮卡也是我爸

297
00:18:13,32 --> 00:18:16,15
I've even got some dads down at work.
我们公司里还有一些我爸爸

298
00:18:16,72 --> 00:18:17,69
That's fine.
没问题

299
00:18:17,96 --> 00:18:22,12
Well,your other dad and I are gonna go have a romantic evening.
你们的另外一个爸爸跟我 要去有一个浪漫的夜晚了

300
00:18:22,36 --> 00:18:24,39
I'll just see you kids around.
孩子们，我们改天见了

301
00:18:24,70 --> 00:18:25,96
Nighty-night.
晚安了

302
00:18:26,17 --> 00:18:27,72
You're not a dad!
你不是一个爸

303
00:18:29,20 --> 00:18:31,47
I can't believe you got us into trouble.
真不敢相信你干的好事

304
00:18:37,51 --> 00:18:39,04
So are you okay?
你还好吗？

305
00:18:41,08 --> 00:18:42,07
Just...
很好…

306
00:18:42,35 --> 00:18:44,82
... I feel like I'm about a hundred.
…我只是觉得自己好老

307
00:18:45,49 --> 00:18:48,15
I thought I was just one of the guys.
我还以为我跟他们一样

308
00:18:48,76 --> 00:18:49,92
Come here.
过来

309
00:18:50,19 --> 00:18:52,82
I'll make you feel like one of the guys.
我会让你觉得 你跟他们一样

310
00:18:58,77 --> 00:19:01,76
For a really cool guy, you suck at foosball.
对一个很酷的人来说 你的足球烂透了

311
00:19:02,77 --> 00:19:04,67
I was killing them.
我痛宰了他们

312
00:19:04,87 --> 00:19:07,10
Yeah,well they suck too.
他们也很烂

313
00:19:10,38 --> 00:19:13,84
You take the poopy diaper and put it in the poopy diaper pail.
对，然后你把有便便的尿布 丢到便便尿布桶里去

314
00:19:14,11 --> 00:19:18,21
Calling it a "poopy diaper" doesn't make this process any cuter.
美其名为便便尿布 并不会让这个过程更可爱

315
00:19:22,42 --> 00:19:24,22
-It's us. -Come on up.
是我们 上来吧

316
00:19:24,42 --> 00:19:26,05
I'll get his stuff together.
我去准备他其他的东西

317
00:19:26,36 --> 00:19:29,30
Okay,we can do this now, can't we,Ben?
我们做得到的，是不是，班？

318
00:19:29,86 --> 00:19:31,30
Yes,we can.
对，我们可以

319
00:19:31,57 --> 00:19:32,76
Yes,we can.
对，我们可以

320
00:19:34,37 --> 00:19:36,77
There! I did it!
好了

321
00:19:37,97 --> 00:19:39,23
I did it!
我换好了

322
00:19:40,24 --> 00:19:42,14
Look at that!
你瞧瞧

323
00:19:42,61 --> 00:19:44,70
It stays on and everything.
紧紧的包在屁屁上

324
00:19:51,75 --> 00:19:55,35
I'm sorry. What did you just say? Did you just say "hi"?
对不起，你刚刚说什么？ 你刚刚说“嗨”啊？

325
00:19:55,56 --> 00:19:58,39
Oh,my God! Ross? Ben just said hi!
天啊，罗斯… 班刚说“嗨”耶

326
00:19:58,63 --> 00:19:59,92
-What? -Ben just said hi!
什么？ 班刚说“嗨”

327
00:20:00,16 --> 00:20:01,59
What,the word "hi"?
什么？嗨那个字？

328
00:20:01,80 --> 00:20:03,63
No,my Uncle Hi.
不，我的嗨舅舅

329
00:20:04,80 --> 00:20:07,60
Great! And I missed that too. I miss everything!
棒透了，我也错过了 我错过一切了

330
00:20:07,83 --> 00:20:11,57
Oh,I'm sorry. I guess I just bring it out in him.
我猜我太有魅力了

331
00:20:12,91 --> 00:20:14,74
-Where is he? -We missed you.
他在哪里？ 我们想你

332
00:20:14,98 --> 00:20:18,47
We missed you so much! Come here,Ben.
我们好想你 过来，班

333
00:20:18,68 --> 00:20:21,15
Guess what? Ben just said his first word.
你们猜，班刚说了哪个字？

334
00:20:22,02 --> 00:20:23,14
What did he say?
他说什么了？

335
00:20:23,42 --> 00:20:24,91
Something about hi.
什么嗨不嗨的

336
00:20:26,15 --> 00:20:29,78
That's so exciting! Mommy's so proud of you!
真是令人兴奋 妈咪好骄傲哦

337
00:20:32,03 --> 00:20:34,15
You know,actually, it's more like,hi!
事实上比较像这样，“嗨”

338
00:20:39,80 --> 00:20:41,50
This could go on for a while.
这可能要玩很久

339
00:20:41,70 --> 00:20:43,69
You're right. We've got a cab waiting.
计程车还在楼下等我们呢

340
00:20:43,94 --> 00:20:45,67
Well,this was fun.
这真好玩 好的

341
00:20:45,87 --> 00:20:49,33
We should do it again sometime,Ben. What do you say?
我们改天一定还要这样子 班，你说怎么样呢？

342
00:20:50,38 --> 00:20:52,94
-All right,so I've got him...? -Tuesday.
好吧，下一次是… 礼拜二

343
00:20:53,45 --> 00:20:54,28
Bye,you guys.
再见了

344
00:20:54,48 --> 00:20:56,47
-Take care. -Bye,Ben.
保重 拜，班

345
00:21:00,39 --> 00:21:02,55
Did he just say "bye"?
他刚刚…他…他刚刚说拜吗？

346
00:21:02,79 --> 00:21:03,95
He said bye!
他说拜…

347
00:21:04,22 --> 00:21:06,19
You said bye! He said bye to me!
你对我说拜，他对我说拜

348
00:21:06,46 --> 00:21:08,33
Yes,he did!
没错

349
00:21:08,56 --> 00:21:11,12
Suddenly I'm seeing him go off to college!
我已经可以幻想他去上大学了

350
00:21:12,30 --> 00:21:15,17
We've gotta go. We've got that cab downstairs.
我们得走了，计程车在楼下等

351
00:21:16,14 --> 00:21:17,36
See you later.
拜拜…

352
00:21:35,12 --> 00:21:38,15
Look at this nice deep hole I dug. Hey,Bert...
我看挖的这个洞好深 柏特…

353
00:21:38,39 --> 00:21:40,62
...isn't this a nice hole here?
…这洞是不是挖得很好？

354
00:21:41,50 --> 00:21:45,99
Ben,this is the part where Ernie buries Bert in the sand and can't find him.
班，这是在演厄尼把柏特 埋在沙里头，然后找不到他

355
00:21:46,63 --> 00:21:51,57
Now,I've looked ahead on the tape, and he does find him again.
现在，我已经先看过了 他后来有找到他

356
00:21:52,84 --> 00:21:56,47
But before that happens, there's some rough going for a while.
可是，在那之前呢 会先有一些让人很难受的

357
00:21:56,68 --> 00:21:58,77
But I think we can handle it.
可是我想我们挺得住

358
00:21:59,08 --> 00:22:04,02
And there's just the alphabet, but we know that ends well,so....
这些只是…只是字母而已 可是我知道结局会很好的…

359
00:22:04,52 --> 00:22:05,68
Here we go.
好，继续了

360
00:22:05,92 --> 00:22:07,48
Bert? Bert?
柏特？… 他刚刚还在这里

361
00:22:09,32 --> 00:22:12,82
What happened to my friend Bert? He was here just a moment ago.
我的朋友柏特怎么了？

362
00:22:13,03 --> 00:22:15,26
Oh,no! My old friend Bert is lost.
不，柏特不见了？

363
00:22:15,50 --> 00:22:17,49
I'm so glad you're here.
我真高兴你在这里

364
00:22:19,77 --> 00:22:21,43
Bye-bye,baby.
拜拜，宝贝

365
00:00:00,00 --> 00:00:00,00


366
